We’ll be adding the @illebrod workshop to our website this week. Very excited to have Martin come over from Oslo to hang out with us. It’ll be held over 2 days. Sunday 7th June we’ll be mixing doughs, covering all the do’s and don’t’s of heirloom and heritage stoneground baking, giving everyone the opportunity to mix a variety of breads using various grains ... spelt/emmer/einkorn/wheat and adding inclusions of porridge or sprouted grain. As a rule Martin only uses inclusions that derive from cereals so we won’t be using any seeds fruits or nuts. We’ll share a nice lunch together and put our little bread babies to sleep. Day 2 will be a shorter session where we will bake our breads, share a breakfast and have an informal Q&A. We’ll have copies of Martins book for sale if you want to get one signed. If you already own a copy you can bring it along on the day and I’m sure he’ll scrawl a little message in it for you. 👍

I love doing this experiment to demonstrate the difference between baking with steam and baking without. One loaf was baked in a fan assisted oven using a combo cooker (@challengerbreadware) and the other just on a tray exposed to the fierce drying power that a fan assisted oven creates. The crust on the loaf on the left sets very quickly and as the dough inside continues to grow it searches for the point of least resistance to keep expanding. So even though the bread has been scored that score quickly bakes and crusts over leaving weak spots prone to blow outs.
One loaf left. This ones coming home with me.
